SIMPLE: levitate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Levitate
<hw>Lev"i*tate</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧v"⟦icr⟧*t⟦amac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>levitas</ets>, <ets>-atis</ets>, lightness. See
<er>Levity</er>.]</ety> <def>To rise, or tend to rise, as if lighter
than the surrounding medium; to become buoyant; -- opposed to
<ant>gravitate</ant>.</def> <rj><au>Sir. J. Herschel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Levitate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Levitate
<hw>Lev"i*tate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Spiritualism)</fld> <def>To
make buoyant; to cause to float in the air; <as>as, to <ex>levitate</ex>
a table</as>.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Levitation</ent>⟦br⟧
